	     <form action="/cgi-bin/mrate.pl" name="f107890162659214">
	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=6447&amp;mid=107890162659214">Anger aug's and aggro weapons</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=6447&amp;mid=107890162659214#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Wed, Mar 10th 1:54 AM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=228459"><span id=" ">Walgurorf</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">15 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>OK this is the deal with the EB proc on the BoC and the Anger range of aggro aug's from LDoN.<br/><br/>1/ No it is not a waste putting anger aug on a BoC<br/>2/ No they don't stack<br/><br/>What I mean by that is on each attack round the system will check if the 1st proc takes effect, now if it does thats it, nothing more will happen untill the next attack round. If however it doesn't proc, it will then check if the 2nd effect takes place (in this case the Anger aug). Therefore the Anger aug will only proc if the Enraging Blow effect doesn't (this is true for all weapons with 2 (Combat) effects, whether it's aggro, DD, slow or whatever).<br/><br/>Effectively adding an Anger aug will at least double the chance of an aggro effect taking place, I say at least double because in my own experience the Anger 3 aug procs more often then the original BoC proc.</p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />EQ1<br/><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=651187 target=akztarg>Walgurorf Beawulfe 67 Barbarian Overlord - Karana</a><br/>Aandaael 58 Dark Elf Necromancer - Karana<br/><br/>EQ2<br/>Chewedon 28 Half Elf Paladin - Innothule<br/>Ahaiphia 19 High Elf Shadow Knight elect - Innothule<br/>Walgurorf 10 Barbarian Summoner - Innothule<br/>Donut 8 Ogre Rogue - Innothule</td></tr>
